Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @prawns{150%grams}. Season with @paprika{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @cucumber{1}(halved lengthways then thinly sliced widthways).

Chop the @tomato{2}(chopped into 2cm chunks).

Trim the @salad leaves{120%grams} and roughly chop.

To a large #bowl{}, add salad leaves, cucumber, tomatoes, @aioli{1%sachet} and @Italian style hard cheese{1%unit}(grated).

Toss until fully combined then season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide the Caesar salad between plates and top with the fried prawns.